You?

latestPosts.caption:
A small flame would be extinguished. A real fire takes what’s thrown at it, and grows.
Marcus Aurelius wrote that.
I’ve had things thrown at me lately. I paused. I bent. But I didn’t break.
The obstacle is the way.
Save this if you know what it means to rise anyway.
